HEADWORD: Nayaur
<hw>Na*yaur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A species of wild sheep (<spn>Ovis Hodgsonii</spn>), native of
Nepal and Tibet. It has a dorsal mane and a white ruff beneath the
neck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nayt</ent>⟦br⟧
